This decrements the count for EACH node in the bubbling loop. So if we bubble up through 5 nodes (from the removed node's parent up to the root), we decrement 5 counts. This accounts for the removed node and all its ancestors.

But wait, I was decrementing the counts in the bubbling loop, and the test is still failing. Let me re-examine my code...

