The core issue is that child counts aren't being decremented correctly during removal. In a proper BST, removing a node should decrement the count for every ancestor that had that node in its subtree. The bubbling loop is supposed to handle this, but something's going wrong - either the counts are being decremented too many times or not at all for certain nodes in the path.

When I trace through what happens after each removal, I need to check whether bubble_up is actually pointing to the right parent at each step. If bubble_up isn't being set correctly after the removal operation, then the subsequent count decrements would apply to the wrong nodes entirely, leaving the tree's metadata inconsistent with its actual structure.

