I found the bug! In lines 466-475, when replacing node with candidate in the parent's child pointer, I'm NOT copying over the child count from node to candidate. The old code at line 469 says:

```rust
let is_left = np_mut.left_child_node.as_ref().map_or(false, |c| Rc::ptr_eq(c, node));
if is_left {
    np_mut.left_child_node = Some(candidate.clone());
} else {
    np_mut.right_child_node = Some(candidate.clone());
}
```

It sets the child pointer but does NOT set the count. Compare with the single-child case (lines 576-582):

```rust
let is_left = np_mut.left_child_node.as_ref().map_or(false, |c| Rc::ptr_eq(c, node));
if is_left {
    np_mut.left_child_node = candidate.clone();
    np_mut.left_child_count = candidate_count;
} else {
    np_mut.right_child_node = candidate.clone();
    np_mut.right_child_count = candidate_count;
}
```

This correctly copies the count. I need to fix this in the two-child case.

