After removing A, if B's left_child_node is still pointing somewhere wrong, the traversal might fail.

I think the issue is with the parent's left_child_count being used for order statistics. The select function relies on left_child_count to determine which node to visit next, so if this count is incorrect, select might skip nodes or go down the wrong path. I need to check if the left_child_count values are being maintained correctly during rotations and deletions.

